## Quick Start
1. [Enable your Github Copilot FTE benefit (model access for free)](https://repos.opensource.microsoft.com/orgs/MicrosoftCopilot); if you cannot login, try this URL:https://github.com/enterprises/microsoft/sso
2. [Download VS code insider](https://code.visualstudio.com/insiders/)
3. [Install git] https://git-scm.com/
4. Clone Repository
   ```
   git clone https://github.com/juanliu_microsoft/pm-studio-mcp.git
   ```
   *Generate token for authentication if needed. Github->Settings->DeveloperSettings->Tokens, check 'repo' scope.*
5. Open terminal on Mac
6. Navigate to your Project Directory
   ```
   cd {path to}/pm-studio-mcp
   ```
7. Install HomeBrew with command
    ```
    /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"
    ```
8. Install Python: `brew install python3`
9. Install uv(python的环境+包管理工具): `brew install uv`
10. Install Dependencies
   ```
   uv sync --all-extras --dev
   ```
11. Create and Activate Virtual Environment
   ```
   # Unix/macOS
   source .venv/bin/activate

   # Windows
   .venv\Scripts\activate
   ```


## Run MCP server locally

1. Create a folder as your workspace, for example, pm-studio-client
2. create a .vscode folder under your client folder
3. create mcp.json under .vscode folder
4. paste the following content to mcp.json
```
{
   "mcpServers": {
        "pm-studio-mcp": {
            "command": "uv",
            "args": [
                "--directory",
                "{path_to_your_MCP_server}/src/pm_studio_mcp",
                "run",
                "main.py"],
            "env": {
                "WORKING_PATH": "{path_to_your_workspace}/working_dir/"
            },
            "disabled": false
        }
   }
}
```
5. cmd+shift+p -> >MCP: List Servers
6. select pm-studio-mcp
7. Start server
8. Open the Github Copilot side panel, change from "Ask" to "Agent" at the bottom-right corner
9. cmd+shift+p -> >Chat: Create Prompt #create a prompt in markdown 
10. Type the prompt in the new markdown file created #you can copy and paste the prompt in "feedback_analysis.prompt.md" in the pm-studio-mcp folder
11. Type "hello" to test
